snippet.textDisplay: So I met this girl a year ago, I showed her that I liked her for 8 months and she said I was her best friend for those 8 months, she told me she fucked someone and I ended up telling her that I liked her the whole time she felt sorry and told me she was all mine, I tried to talk to her in a more loving way for the next 2 weeks and she wouldn’t really text or say much, she would still refer to me as her best friend, so I assumed that she was either not into me the way she said she was, noticed that we we’re better off as friends, or she was going through some stuff that she needed time on instead of putting time into a relationship(which I understand), so she didn’t really text me any more. 3 months ago another girl appeared out of no where, we we’re just friends, she was going through some tough time. We ended up talking more and we fell in love, it wasn’t that easy tho, I was still in love with the girl I met a year ago, I  moved on because I thought it was for the best of us, especially for her. Now I’m into my most recent relationship (the one I started to talk with 3 months ago) so seriously because we connected so well, it’s probably the best relationship I’ve had ever. I decided to text the girl I met 1 year ago and let her know about me and how I was moving on and for her to not take it a bad way or think I’m rejecting her. I thought she would support me through it because I thought we would still be best friends because we’ve been through so much.  But that was just in a perfect world. What actually happened is she ended up hating me, I asked her why she didn’t text me for the next couple of months after I told her I liked her. She told me that she was in the hospital because she wanted to kill her self. I asked her why she didn’t tell me and she said she didn’t tell anyone, I told her that it was both our faults due to miscommunication but she didn’t want to understand. She was crying on her Snapchat story and posted this song so I came to see what she was feeling and I’m genuinely so sorry but I told her that this was one of those things you wish you could go back in time to fix but that is impossible, i started a new relationship and I wanted to be loyal to her, I told her I didn’t mean to hurt her and that I still really care about her. After all she is still my friend even if I’m not hers. I hope everyone can learn to communicate with their friends, family, and partners because this could’ve all been prevented by either me asking or her telling me. Thank you and I really appreciate you if you read all of it 🙏

We ended up talking more and we fell in love, it wasn’t that easy tho, I was still in love with the girl I met a year ago, I  moved on because I thought it was for the best of us, especially for her. Now I’m into my most recent relationship (the one I started to talk with 3 months ago) so seriously because we connected so well, it’s probably the best relationship I’ve had ever. I decided to text the girl I met 1 year ago and let her know about me and how I was moving on and for her to not take it a bad way or think I’m rejecting her. I thought she would support me through it because I thought we would still be best friends because we’ve been through so much.  But that was just in a perfect world. What actually happened is she ended up hating me, I asked her why she didn’t text me for the next couple of months after I told her I liked her. She told me that she was in the hospital because she wanted to kill her self. I asked her why she didn’t tell me and she said she didn’t tell anyone, I told her that it was both our faults due to miscommunication but she didn’t want to understand. She was crying on her Snapchat story and posted this song so I came to see what she was feeling and I’m genuinely so sorry but I told her that this was one of those things you wish you could go back in time to fix but that is impossible, i started a new relationship and I wanted to be loyal to her, I told her I didn’t mean to hurt her and that I still really care about her. After all she is still my friend even if I’m not hers. I hope everyone can learn to communicate with their friends, family, and partners because this could’ve all been prevented by either me asking or her telling me. Thank you and I really appreciate you if you read all of it 🙏
